  "local_port": 33810,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I do if I graduated from uni 11 years ago and had only found work two years after for only a few months?",
  "response": "Finding yourself in this situation can be challenging, but there are several proactive steps you can take to improve your circumstances and increase your employability:\n\n1. **Assess Your Skills and Interests**:\n   - Reflect on what skills you have acquired since graduation.\n   - Identify your interests and strengths to determine what types of jobs you would enjoy and be good at.\n\n2. **Update Your Resume and LinkedIn Profile**:\n   - Highlight any relevant skills, volunteer work, freelance projects, or courses you\u2019ve completed.\n   - Make sure your resume is current and accurately reflects your experiences and abilities.\n\n3. **Networking**:\n   - Reach out to former classmates, professors, and colleagues for advice and possible job leads.\n   - Attend industry events, job fairs, and professional meetups to expand your network.\n   - Utilize LinkedIn to connect with professionals in your field.\n\n4. **Learning and Skill Building**:\n   - Take online courses or certifications to update your skills in your chosen industry.\n   - Consider returning to school for additional qualifications if financially and practically feasible.\n   - Stay informed about trends and developments in your field.\n\n5. **Temporary or Part-time Work**:\n   - Consider freelancing, internships, or volunteering to gain experience.\n   - Temporary roles can provide valuable experience and help build your resume.\n\n6. **Career Counseling and Job Placement Services**:\n   - Consult a career counselor for tailored advice and support.\n   - Use job placement services and workforce agencies that may offer training programs or job-matching services.\n\n7. **Reevaluate Your Career Path**:\n   - If you find it difficult to get employment in your desired field, consider pivoting to a different career that utilizes your skills.\n   - Research industries that are growing and actively hiring.\n\n8. **Persistence and Adaptability**:\n   - Be prepared to face challenges and rejections; persistence is key.\n   - Adapt your job search strategy based on feedback and experiences.\n\n9. **Self-Care and Mental Health**:\n   - Take care of your mental and physical health. Job searching is often stressful, so make sure to maintain a balanced lifestyle.\n   - Seek support from friends, family, or a therapist if needed.\n\nTaking these steps can help you increase your chances of finding a suitable and fulfilling job.",
